Package com.linecorp.armeria.server

Interface PathMappingContext

  • public interface PathMappingContext
    Holds the parameters which are required to find a service available to handle the request.

      • consumeType

        @Nullable
MediaType consumeType()
        Returns MediaType specified by 'Content-Type' header of the request.

      • produceTypes

        @Nullable
List<MediaType> produceTypes()
        Returns a list of MediaType that is ordered by client-side preferences. It only includes the media types supported by the virtual host. null would be returned if the virtual host does not support media type negotiation.

      • summary

        List<Object> summary()
        Returns an identifier of this PathMappingContext instance. It would be used as a cache key to reduce pattern list traversal.

      • delayThrowable

        void delayThrowable​(Throwable cause)
        Delays throwing a Throwable until reaching the end of the service list.

      • delayedThrowable

        Optional<Throwable> delayedThrowable()
        Returns a delayed Throwable set before via delayThrowable(Throwable).

      • overridePath

        default PathMappingContext overridePath​(String path)
        Returns a wrapped PathMappingContext which holds the specified path. It is usually used to find a Service with a prefix-stripped path.

      • isCorsPreflight

        boolean isCorsPreflight()
        Returns true if this context is for a CORS preflight request.
        See Also:
        ArmeriaHttpUtil.isCorsPreflightRequest(HttpRequest)
